# Repository Registry

**Check `WORKERS.md` for the full registry before pushing to or linking any repo.**

## Application repos

| Environment | Repo | Git remote |
|-------------|------|------------|
| Production | `typekpaco2002/mdlcln` (note: `mdlcln`, not `mdcln`) | `typekpaco` |
| Testing / staging | `mconqeuroror/mdcln-testing` | `mtesting` |

## Worker repos

| Worker | Repo | Local path |
|--------|------|-----------|
| RunPod NSFW image worker | `mconqeuroror/mdclnworker` | *(deploy from repo)* |
| RunPod motion worker (MotionX / NSFW motion) | `mconqeuroror/motion` | `runpod-mdcln-motion/` |
| Hetzner FFmpeg worker | **no git repo** | `ffmpeg-worker-deploy/` |

## Rules

- Never push worker source code that lives in its own repo as if it belongs to the main app repo, and vice versa.
- `ffmpeg-worker-deploy/` is the **only** worker bundle kept in this monorepo; it has no upstream git repo — deploy it as a zip to Hetzner/EasyPanel.
- To update the motion worker local mirror: `git -C runpod-mdcln-motion pull` (upstream is `mconqeuroror/motion`).
- When adding a new worker, update **`WORKERS.md`** before opening a PR.
